time sharing in a traffic control program.wthe toronto traffic signal control system consistsof a variety of logically distinct computer programs, all competing for machine time.  to satisfythese demands, a time-sharing program has been written whose purpose is to execute, in the order of apredefined priority, the various subprograms within the real-time system.  in this paper the more interestingaspects of the time-sharing program are outlined.cacm november, green, l. e. s.ca jb march ,   : pm